The paper deals with entity resolution, which is a problem in data integration and falls under the database (cs.DB) sub-category. The paper proposes a machine learning-based approach for entity resolution, which involves feature engineering and training data creation, indicating the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The paper also discusses the use of distributed representation-based approaches, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DB, cs.AI, and cs.LG, followed by cs.IR and cs.CL.
